# cargo-fuzz build output + the auto-grown corpus / crash artifacts.
# The dictionaries that ARE committed live under `dictionaries/`
# (tracked); everything below is scratch.
#
# NOTE: `Cargo.lock` is NOT ignored — it is committed.  This crate is a
# SEPARATE workspace (excluded from `runtime`), so without a tracked
# lockfile the `ci-fuzz.yml` runners would resolve `libfuzzer-sys` /
# `arbitrary` / the transitive deps afresh on every clean checkout, and
# an unrelated upstream release could break or change the fuzz gate —
# defeating the harness's pinning intent.  A committed lockfile pins them.
target/
corpus/
artifacts/
coverage/
